listitem.para:
Syntactic sugar for writing nested attribute sets.  Instead of


{
  foo = {
    bar = 123;
    xyzzy = true;
  };
  a = { b = { c = "d"; }; };
}


    you can write


{
  foo.bar = 123;
  foo.xyzzy = true;
  a.b.c = "d";
}


    This is useful, for instance, in NixOS configuration files.
